    <body>
      <section eId="sec_2999_V">
        <num>2999-V</num>
        <heading>Eligibility and enrollment</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2999_V__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2999_V__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>be at least fifty-five years old;\n  (ii) meet the eligibility requirements for a nursing home level of\ncare;\n  (iii) reside within the PACE organization's approved service area;\n  (iv) be able to be maintained safely in the community-based setting\nwith the assistance of the PACE organization; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2999_V__subsec_v">
          <num>(v)</num>
          <content>
            <p>meet any additional program specific eligibility conditions\nimposed under the PACE program agreement between the PACE organization,\nthe department, and CMS; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2999_V__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>be otherwise eligible to participate in a PACE demonstration or\nspecialty program authorized by the federal PACE Innovation Act and\napproved by the department and CMS.\n  2. Enrollment in a PACE organization shall be voluntary for the\neligible individual.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
